getLastSyncTimeInUTC

public Calendar getLastSyncTimeInUTC()
Gets the last time that you requested a download. The date and time is expressed in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC). Typically, you request a full download the first time you call the operation by setting this element to null. On all subsequent calls you set the last sync time to the time stamp of the previous download. The download file contains the time stamp of the download in the SyncTime column of the Account record. Use the time stamp to set LastSyncTimeInUTC the next time that you request a download. If you specify the last sync time, only those entities that have changed (been updated or deleted) since the specified date and time will be downloaded. However, if the campaign data has not been previously downloaded, the operation performs a full download.

Returns:
